    "description": "<p>A taser is a weapon that uses springs or compressed air to fire a pair of darts at a target. On impact, the darts release a powerful electrical current. Tasers are simple weapons and require no feats to use. On a successful hit with a X26, X2, X3, and C3, the darts deal electricity damage and the target must make a Fortitude Saving Throw [TN15] or be paralyzed for 1d6 rounds. On a successful hit with a Taser 7, the darts deal electricity damage and the target must make a Fortitude Saving Throw [TN20] or be paralyzed for 1d3 rounds. Reloading a taser costs 3 Combat Points that provokes AoO. All tasers come with 3 extra cartridges. Tasers can also be used as stun gun by removing the cartridge, which cost 1 CP. When using them in this manner, they are considered simple melee weapons, and have the same damage and effect as if it were used as a ranged weapon. Tasers cannot provoke a critical strike. The X26 and the X2 taser have a single tactical upgrade slot that can be outfitted with multiple ranged upgrades, and the Taser 7 has a built in standard laser sight and standard tactical flashlight. For the purpose of non-proficiency feats, tasers are considered handguns with detachable magazines.</p>",
